criteria.driver_alignment:
Represent — student framed the analysis and the need to evaluate impact of additional debt;  
Implement — student executed a before/after scenario (baseline WACC and WACC after $3B issuance) and reported numeric change;  
Validate — student interpreted the result and noted its magnitude and implications.

Represent — mapped WACC to a firmwide discount rate and project‑level adjustments;  
Implement — applied WACC as the hurdle in capital‑budgeting contexts (US vs international content) and linked financing choice to project funding;  
Evolve/Reflect — recommended capital‑structure strategy to lower WACC and discussed implications for investment decisions.

Reflect — articulated the trade‑off theory and implications for WACC;  
Implement — demonstrated with numeric before/after WACC and leverage results;  
Evolve — translated analysis into a concrete capital‑structure recommendation (15–20% target, caution vs. 30%).
